ProtoResult:
. "Let $p$ be any prime number and suppose that $p \notdivide 
   a$. Then \[ a^{p-1} \equiv 1 \pmod{ p }. \] Furthermore, for
   any integer $b$, $b^p \equiv b \pmod{ p}$."
